layers.name: geonode:pgrm2958_mwlassrural202021_whanganui_epsg3857
layers.description:
Outputpgrm2958-MWLASSRural202021 - Rural 0.30 m GSD Ortho imagery captured 2020/2021 season.

Aerial photography was captured over the MWLASS rural area totaling approximately 22,901 km2

The area of capture comprises the Manawatu-Wanganui Region of the North Island.
During the 2020/2021 season 73% of the region was captured and the remaining aerial imagery scheduled for capture during the 2021/2022 season.

Whanganui Districts is partially captured, main areas missing include the majority of the Whanganui National Park and some parts of the western boundary.
layers.title: 2021 Rural Photography Flown 2021

layers.name: geonode:aerial_photo_1965_3857_urban
layers.description: Orthophotography of Survey Number 1791.  The Aerial Photography for SN1791 was acquired using a WILD RC8 camera system on 29th October 1965. The imagery was collected flying 16,500 feet above sea level providing an approximate scale of 1:24,000. The original scanned images provide an approximate raw GSD of 0.343 m which has been resampled to 0.32 m in order for the pixels to fit within the tile size as whole pixels.  Imagery supplied by SKYVUW Ltd.
layers.title: 1965 Urban Aerial Photo 1965 EPSG3857
